A:
_Z7averageP
_Z7averageif

B:
output:
1 8
4 8
4 8
8 8

sizeof(char) is 1 by definition (so a char is a byte). 
int occupies 4 bytes.
Single-precision floating-point format occupies 4 bytes.
Double-precision floating-point format occupies 8 bytes
Size of a pointer should be 8 bytes on any 64-bit C/C++ compiler.
